        public void configure​(Size size)
        Configures the minimum/maximum size of the XML document. This method is not usually invoked directly. Instead, use the `@Size` annotation on fuzzed parameters to configure automatically.
        Parameters:
        size - the min/max size of the XML document

      • configure

        public void configure​(Dictionary dict)
               throws IOException
        Configures the string generator used by this generator to use a dictionary. This is useful for overriding the default arbitrary string generator with something that pulls tag names from a predefined list.
        Parameters:
        dict - the dictionary file
        Throws:
        IOException - if the dictionary file cannot be read
